                    "title": "I-adjective + です",
                    "short_description": "Polite i-adjective form",
                    "md_description": "## I-adjective + です — Polite Form\n\n### What are i-adjectives?\n\n**I-adjectives** end in `い` in their dictionary form: `高い` (expensive), `寒い` (cold), `面白い` (interesting). They conjugate independently — `です` only adds politeness.\n\n> ⚠️ `です` after an i-adjective is just a politeness marker, not a copula. Never change the `い` before `です`.\n\n---\n\n### Formation\n\n```\n[i-adjective\n] + です\n高い → 高いです (it's expensive)\n寒い → 寒いです (it's cold)\n面白い → 面白いです (it's interesting)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Full conjugation table\n\n| Form | Japanese | Meaning |\n|------|----------|---------|\n| Present (+) | `高いです` | it's expensive |\n| Present (-) | `高くないです` | it's not expensive |\n| Past (+) | `高かったです` | it was expensive |\n| Past (-) | `高くなかったです` | it wasn't expensive |\n\n---\n\n### Examples\n\n```\nこの映画は面白いです。\nThis movie is interesting.\n```\n\n```\n今日は寒いですね。\nIt's cold today, isn't it?\n```\n\n```\nこのケーキはおいしいです！\nThis cake is delicious!\n```\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Exception: `いい` shifts to `よい` when conjugated\n\n| Form | Correct |\n|------|---------|\n| Present | `いいです` |\n| Negative | `よくないです` ✅ (NOT `いくないです` ❌) |\n| Past | `よかったです` ✅ (NOT `いかったです` ❌) |\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Key insight\n\nI-adjectives carry the full meaning on their own. `です` is just a polite \"coat\" draped over the adjective."
