                    "short_description": "Te-form of i-adjective",
                    "md_description": "## I-adjective Te-form: ～くて\n\n### What is it?\n\n`～くて` is the **te-form of i-adjectives**, used to:\n1. List multiple adjectives\n2. Express a reason or cause\n\n---\n\n### Formation\n\n```\n[i-adjective\n] → drop い + くて\n高い → 高くて\n面白い → 面白くて\nおいしい → おいしくて\n```\n\n---\n\n### Use 1: Listing adjectives\n\n```\nこの料理はおいしくて、安いです。\nThis dish is delicious and cheap.\n```\n\n```\n彼女は優しくて、頭がいいです。\nShe's kind and smart.\n```\n\n---\n\n### Use 2: Expressing reason\n\n```\n頭が痛くて、学校を休みました。\nI had a headache, so I missed school.\n```\n\n```\n忙しくて、電話できませんでした。\nI was busy and couldn't call.\n```\n\n---\n\n### Exception: `いい → よくて`\n\n```\n✅ この映画はよくて、もう一度見たいです。\n❌ いくて\n```\n\n---\n\n### Te-form comparison\n\n| Type | Dictionary form | Te-form |\n|------|----------------|---------|\n| I-adjective | 高い | `高くて` |\n| Na-adjective | 静か | `静かで` |\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Key point\n\nWhen listing adjectives with `くて`, the order doesn't imply temporal sequence — it's just enumeration or causal connection."
