                    "md_description": "## Na-adjective Te-form: ～で\n\n### What is it?\n\n`～で` is the **te-form of na-adjectives** — used to list qualities or express a cause/reason. It's derived the same way as `です` → `で`.\n\n---\n\n### Formation\n\n```\n[na-adjective\n] + で\n静か → 静かで\n有名 → 有名で\n便利 → 便利で\n```\n\n---\n\n### Use 1: Listing qualities\n\n```\n彼女は親切で、真面目です。\nShe's kind and hardworking.\n```\n\n```\nこの街は静かで、きれいです。\nThis city is quiet and beautiful.\n```\n\n---\n\n### Use 2: Expressing reason\n\n```\n病気で、学校を休みました。\nI was sick, so I missed school.\n```\n\n```\nこの店は有名で、いつも混んでいます。\nThis shop is famous, so it's always crowded.\n```\n\n---\n\n### Te-form comparison\n\n| Type | Dictionary form | Te-form |\n|------|----------------|---------|\n| I-adjective | 高い | `高くて` |\n| Na-adjective | 静か | `静かで` |\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Don't confuse with particle で\n\n`で` as te-form of na-adjective ≠ particle で (location/means). Context always clarifies.\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Tip\n\n`静かで` and `静かな` are two functions of the same word:\n- `静かな部屋` (noun modifier)\n- `部屋は静かで、快適です` (te-form linking clauses)"
