                    "title": "Causative form",
                    "short_description": "Make someone do",
                    "md_description": "## Causative Form — \"Make/Let Someone Do\"\n\n### What is it?\n\nThe **causative form** expresses that someone **makes** or **lets** another person do something.\n\n---\n\n### Formation\n\n**Group 1:** u-row → a-row + せる\n```\n飲む → 飲ませる (make drink)\n書く → 書かせる (make write)\n話す → 話させる (make speak)\n```\n\n**Group 2:** drop る + させる\n```\n食べる → 食べさせる (make eat)\n見る → 見させる (make watch)\n```\n\n**Group 3:**\n```\nする → させる (make do)\n来る → 来させる (make come)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Sentence structure\n\n```\n[Causer\n] は/が [Person\n] を/に [causative verb\n]\n先生は学生に漢字を書かせました。\nThe teacher made the students write kanji.\n```\n\n---\n\n### Examples\n\n**Making (compulsion):**\n```\n母は私に野菜を食べさせました。\nMy mom made me eat vegetables.\n```\n\n**Letting (permission):**\n```\n先生は学生を早く帰らせました。\nThe teacher let the students go home early.\n```\n\n**First-person intent:**\n```\nやらせてください！\nPlease let me do it!\n```\n\n---\n\n### Causative-passive\n\n`飲む → 飲まされる` (be forced to drink):\n```\n上司に残業させられました。\nMy boss made me work overtime.\n```\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Tip\n\nWhen something causes an emotion or a non-volitional state, use `を`:\n```\n彼女は私を心配させます。(She makes me worry.)\n```"
