                    "md_description": "## Form ～すぎる — \"Too much\" / \"Excessively\"\n\n### What is it?\n\n`～すぎる` expresses **excess** — doing or being something too much or too extremely.\n\n---\n\n### Formation\n\n**Verbs:** ます-stem + すぎる\n```\n食べます → 食べすぎる (eat too much)\n飲みます → 飲みすぎる (drink too much)\n働きます → 働きすぎる (work too much)\n```\n\n**I-adjectives:** drop い + すぎる\n```\n高い → 高すぎる (too expensive)\n難しい → 難しすぎる (too difficult)\n```\n\n**Na-adjectives:** + すぎる\n```\n静か → 静かすぎる (too quiet)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Examples\n\n```\n昨日食べすぎて、お腹が痛いです。\nI ate too much yesterday and my stomach hurts.\n```\n\n```\nこのバッグは高すぎます。\nThis bag is too expensive.\n```\n\n```\n日本語は難しすぎて、諦めそうです。\nJapanese is so difficult I feel like giving up.\n```\n\n```\n飲みすぎないでください。\nPlease don't drink too much.\n```\n\n---\n\n### ～すぎ as a noun\n\nDrop る to use as a noun:\n```\n食べすぎはよくないです。(Overeating is not good.)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Key nuance\n\n`すぎる` always carries a **negative connotation** — even good qualities become a flaw when excessive:\n```\n優しすぎる。(Too kind → that's a problem!)\n```"
