                    "md_description": "## Form ～そう (i-adjective) — \"Looks/Seems...\"\n\n### What is it?\n\n`～そう` after an adjective expresses a **visual or sensory impression** — \"looks like,\"\"seems like,\" based on what you directly observe.\n\n---\n\n### Formation\n\n**I-adjectives:** drop い + そう\n```\nおいしい → おいしそう (looks delicious)\n難しい → 難しそう (looks difficult)\n重い → 重そう (looks heavy)\n```\n\n**Na-adjectives:** + そう\n```\n元気 → 元気そう (looks energetic/healthy)\n便利 → 便利そう (looks convenient)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Examples\n\n```\nこのケーキはおいしそうです。\nThis cake looks delicious.\n```\n\n```\n彼は元気そうです。\nHe looks well.\n```\n\n```\nあの荷物は重そうですね。\nThat luggage looks heavy, doesn't it?\n```\n\n```\nこの問題は難しそうだ。\nThis problem looks difficult.\n```\n\n---\n\n### As a noun modifier\n\n`～そうな + noun`:\n```\nおいしそうなケーキ (a cake that looks delicious)\n```\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Exceptions\n\n```\nいい → よさそう (looks good) — NOT いそう!\nない → なさそう (seems like there isn't) — NOT なそう!\n```\n\n---\n\n### Contrast with ～ようだ\n\n| Form | Nuance |\n|------|--------|\n| `おいしそう` | Visual/sensory impression |\n| `おいしいようだ` | Based on evidence or reasoning |"
