                    "short_description": "Becomes (verb)",
                    "md_description": "## Form ～になる — \"Become\"\n\n### What is it?\n\n`～になる` expresses a **change of state** — \"become something/someone.\" Used with nouns and na-adjectives.\n\n---\n\n### Formation\n\n```\n[noun/na-adjective\n] + になる\n先生 → 先生になる (become a teacher)\n有名 → 有名になる (become famous)\n便利 → 便利になる (become convenient)\n```\n\n> For i-adjectives: use `～くなる` (separate entry)\n\n---\n\n### Examples\n\n```\n将来、医者になりたいです。\nI want to become a doctor in the future.\n```\n\n```\n彼は有名な作家になりました。\nHe became a famous author.\n```\n\n```\n秋になると、葉が赤くなります。\nWhen autumn comes, the leaves turn red.\n```\n\n```\nこの街は便利になりましたね。\nThis city has become more convenient, hasn't it?\n```\n\n---\n\n### Adjective comparison\n\n| Type | Form | Example |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Noun | ～になる | `先生になる` |\n| Na-adjective | ～になる | `有名になる` |\n| I-adjective | ～くなる | `暑くなる` |\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Key verb to master\n\n`なる` (to become) is foundational — it combines with `ように`, `こと`, and many other patterns to create essential grammar structures."
